  "body": "I'm working with kubernetes 1.0.1 on AWS.\n\nCurrently, the way to specify custom docker options for the docker daemon on the minion machine is to set the EXTRA_DOCKER_OPTS environment variable when raising the cluster.\nThe problem is that if I also set the KUBE_ENABLE_INSECURE_REGISTRY environment variable it overrides the EXTRA_DOCKER_OPTS here:\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/v1.0.1/cluster/aws/config-default.sh#L70\n\nI need the custom options in order to set `--default-ulimit nofile` on the docker daemon.\n\nDoes it make sense to only append to EXTRA_DOCKER_OPTS when KUBE_ENABLE_INSECURE_REGISTRY is set instead of override? This way users will be able to set whatever custom docker options they would like in conjunction with KUBE_ENABLE_INSECURE_REGISTRY.\n",
